						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone leaning against the back wall of the temple of Kiṭṭada Hanumān.</hi></p>						

						<p>The purport of this damaged record is not clear. The names, <hi rend="bold">Paraśurāma</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Indra</hi> are found. A certain <hi rend="bold">Dōra</hi> seems to have erected the stone.</p>						

						<p>The characters are of about <hi rend="bold">9th century A.D.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
